            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "As a parent of a K0 student at GGIS Bavdhan, I can confidently say that choosing this school has been one of the best decisions for our child.\n\nI still vividly remember my son’s first day at school—he was extremely scared, anxious, and created quite a scene. As parents, it was overwhelming for us too. However, the way Aparna Ma’am, the Academic Coordinator, handled the entire situation—with such calmness, patience, and reassurance—not only comforted our child but also gave us immense confidence. In that very moment, we knew that our son was in safe and caring hands.\n\nTalking about his class teacher, Sneha Teacher—fondly called “meri Sneha Teacher” by my son—she has completely transformed his perception of school. Today, he is excited to go to school every single day. The level of care and attention she provides is truly remarkable. From remembering what he brings in his tiffin, to building his confidence, to noticing how much he eats, how much he talks, and understanding what he likes and dislikes—not just in school but beyond—her attention to every little detail reflects her deep involvement and genuine love for the children. We are incredibly grateful for the unconditional warmth and support she has shown our son.\n\nThe entire school environment deserves appreciation. The administration and all pre-primary teachers are equally welcoming, approachable, and supportive. What truly stands out is that every teacher seems to know each child personally. There is a strong sense of community where teachers, staff, and parents work together with openness and mutual respect.\n\nGGIS Bavdhan is not just focused on academics but also on nurturing values through everyday actions. This balance of education and value-building is what makes the school truly special.\n\nI wholeheartedly recommend GGIS Bavdhan to all parents in and around the Bavdhan area. It is a place where children are not only educated but also cared for, understood, and shaped into better individuals.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
